    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "If you installed using the .deb package, normal Linux .deb uninstallation instructions should apply. http://askubuntu.com/questions/22200/how-to-uninstall-a-deb-package\n\n@MaximoTrinidad - does `sudo apt-get remove powershell` not work for uninstalling powershell? \n\nAs far as OSX goes, there is no default package manager that I'm aware of for uninstallation, it will need to be manually uninstalled. \n",
