    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Likewise for `yum` on CentOS/RHEL: `sudo yum remove powershell` per [RedHat's docs](https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-US/Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux/6/html/Deployment_Guide/sec-Removing.html).\n\nIn essence, when you install a Linux package, you then uninstall it using the Linux package manager.\n\nOS X's packages are notoriously annoying because they don't support automatic removal; but this is another issue (and we intend to replace PKGs with brewfiles).\n\nThanks for your interest!\n",
